node.text:
We get into trouble when we start relying on our partners to be responsible for any of the above. A consistently supportive partner is one who is also able to manage their own emotions and feelings. 

What else do you feel a partner is / is not responsible for? 🗣🔥

This doesn’t apply to abusive partners who mess with your feelings. I’ll also add that we are all responsible for how we treat others and what types of behaviors we choose to tolerate from others in our lives ❤️❤️❤️

node.text:
What are some key signs that your mental health is declining? 

Becoming aware of when our mental health might be declining is key in being able to take back control with self care or seeking help and support 🗣🔥

node.text:
What else should people probably not make jokes about? 

Obviously, humor and laughing are important. Everyone will have a different opinion on what is “ok” and not ok to make jokes about, but generally this list could potentially be really hurtful to others. It’s almost impossible to know who might be struggling with some of these behind the scenes. 

The way I see it, there is a line of humorous intimacy that should be considered in every relationship or environment. For example if you go to a comedy club with your close friends, you might be able to get away with more risqué jokes than if you are at the office with people you just met and work with. 

Anyways, always be kind! It’s 100% possible to be funny or make people laugh without potentially hurting others on a deep level with certain jokes 🗣🔥
